summary: Wade: Tony, I think you and I have so much in common. We see something we want and just dive in and we take it. Know what I...
body:
Wade: Tony, I think you and I have so much in common. We see something we want and just dive in and we take it. Know what I mean?

Tony: Yeah…

Wade: Which is why…on Christmas Day… I’m going to ask Peter to marry me.

Tony: *???*

Wade: And I know how tight you two are.

Tony: Mm-hmm…

Wade: So I’d really, really like your blessing.

Tony: Uh, Deadpool… Really appreciate you coming to me. But, uh, the answer is no.

Wade: Dude, I’m so confused. What the fuck? What the hell? This went so much differently when I rehearsed it with Clint. Yeah. I asked you and you were like, “Yeah dude. My son”

Tony: *what??!?!!?*

Wade: Why don’t you give me a few days to win you over, okay? And by Christmas morning… I promise you’re going to be calling me “son”. I’m gonna be calling you “Dad”.

Tony: Don’t think that’s going to happen.

Wade: I think it’s gonna, Dad.

Tony: *looking at Wade* Don’t.

Wade: Dad, come on.

Tony: Don’t call me “Dad”.

Wade: Don’t call you “Dad”?

Tony: I’m not your dad.

Wade: I mean, you’re gonna be my dad.

Tony: No. No.

Wade: What, Dad?

Tony: *shook* Okay, now you’re playing with me.

Wade: All right… Dad.

summary: even though i know tony was saying ‘it’s always you’ to pepper i can’t help but feel he’s also saying it to the iron man mask....
body: even though i know tony was saying ‘it’s always you’ to pepper i can’t help but feel he’s also saying it to the iron man mask. even though tony believes his life is over, that this is all his fault and he’s all on his own, iron man saved his life. iron man saved a lot of people. without iron man, he would’ve never been with pepper, he would’ve never met peter, he would’ve never became an avenger, without iron man he wouldn’t be who he is and even though it’s the end of the world, the end of his world, iron man will always be there and will always be a part of him, even at the end of his life when he’s all alone

Maybe that’s the reason why Cap says “is this an old message?” and looks so surprised, because if you think about that, he has no reason. They didn’t know that he stuck in quantum realm, they did’t know if he alive or dead. If this were happening at the moment they would probably just decided that he came here to help, but would not be so surprised.
